subSection.paragraph:
The genus
Aureoboletus Pouzar (1957: 48)
( Boletaceae , Boletales ) was proposed in 1957 with its type species
A. gentilis (Quél. 1884: 504) Pouzar (1957: 48)
. This genus can be distinguished from other genera in Boletaceae by a viscid or dry pileus and a brilliant yellow hymenophore that does not change color when injured ( Klofac 2010 ;
Wu et al . 2016
;
Zhang et al . 2019
).
Aureoboletus species
typically form close symbiotic relationships with trees in the families Fagaceae and Pinaceae ( Pouzar 1957 ; Klofac 2010 ;
Wu et al . 2016
;
Zhang et al . 2019
). This genus, like other boletes, has received much attention from mycologists for its species richness. Approximately 49 species of
Aureoboletus
have been described to date (
Yang et al . 2003
; Klofac 2010 ; Shi & Liu 2013 ;
Zhang et al . 2014
, 2015a , b, 2017, 2019;
Halling et al . 2015
;
Zeng et al . 2015
;
Wu et al. 2016
; Kuo & Ortiz-Santana 2020;
Wang et al . 2020
; Farid et al . 2021) and 25 of them occur in China (
Yang et al . 2003
; Shi & Liu 2013 ;
Zhang et al . 2014
, 2015a , b, 2017, 2019;
Zeng et al . 2015
;
Wu et al . 2016
;
Wang et al . 2020
).

DNA extraction and polymerase chain reaction (PCR) procedures followed those of
Zeng et al . (2013
, 2017 , 2018 ) and references therein. Primer pairs used for amplification were: LR0R/LR5 ( Vilgalys & Hester 1990 ;
James et al . 2006
) for the nuclear ribosomal large subunit RNA (28 S ); ITS 5/ ITS 4 (White et al . 1990) for the nuc rDNA region encompassing the internal transcribed spacers 1 and 2, along with the 5.8S rDNA ( ITS ); EF1-2F/EF1-2R (
Zeng et al. 2013
) for the translation elongation factor 1-α gene (
TEF 1
); and bRPB2-6F/bRPB2-7.1R (Matheny 2013) for the RNA polymerase II second largest subunit gene ( RPB2 ). The PCR thermal cycling programs for 28 S , ITS ,
TEF 1
, and RPB2 amplification were conducted as follows: 95 ° C for 4 min, 35 cycles of 94 ° C for 60 s, an appropriate temperature (50 ° C for 28 S and ITS , 53 ° C for
TEF 1
, and 52 ° C for RPB2 ) for 60 s, 72 ° C for 4 min, and 72 ° C for 5 min. The PCR products were purified (TIANGEN, Beijing , P .R. China ) and then sequenced using a BigDye Terminator v3.1 Kit and an ABI 3730xl DNA Analyzer (Guangzhou Branch of BGI, P .R. China ). BioEdit v7.0.9 ( Hall 1999 ) was used to compile DNA sequences; the sequences were then deposited in GenBank ( Table 1 ).

